title: Google\Cloud\Dlp\V2\Container
name: Container
description:
Represents a container that may contain DLP findings.

Examples of a container include a file, table, or database record.

Generated from protobuf message google.privacy.dlp.v2.Container

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.type
params.description: Container type, for example BigQuery or Cloud Storage.

params.name: data.project_id
params.description: Project where the finding was found. Can be different from the project that owns the finding.

params.name: data.full_path
params.description: A string representation of the full container name. Examples: - BigQuery: 'Project:DataSetId.TableId' - Cloud Storage: 'gs://Bucket/folders/filename.txt'

params.name: data.root_path
params.description: The root of the container. Examples: - For BigQuery table project_id:dataset_id.table_id, the root is dataset_id - For Cloud Storage file gs://bucket/folder/filename.txt, the root is gs://bucket

params.name: data.relative_path
params.description: The rest of the path after the root. Examples: - For BigQuery table project_id:dataset_id.table_id, the relative path is table_id - For Cloud Storage file gs://bucket/folder/filename.txt, the relative path is folder/filename.txt

params.name: data.update_time
params.description: Findings container modification timestamp, if applicable. For Cloud Storage, this field contains the last file modification timestamp. For a BigQuery table, this field contains the last_modified_time property. For Datastore, this field isn't populated.

params.name: data.version
params.description: Findings container version, if available ("generation" for Cloud Storage).
